Cottura:

1. Soffriggere scalogno a piacere in un filo d'olio;
2. Sistemare nella padella gli involtini;
3. Far dorare l'infarinatura da entrambi i lati;
4. Aggiungere il vino bianco;
5. Seguire la cottura ed aggiungere del vino onde evitare che gli involtini si asciughino prima che la carne sia ben cotta.

1. Fry minced 1 onion and 2 carrots in olive oil until they golden;
2. Add beef stuffing and continue to fry 7-10 minutes;
3. Add oregano, basil, salt and pepper;
4. Cut tomatoes from can and add to the stuffing;
5. Pour some tomato sauce and let the stuffing simmer for about 15 minutes;
6. Boil lasagna sheets in salted water 2-3 minutes each;
7. Lay the first sheet in the deep pan, put some stuffing, pour some heavy cream and top with cheese;
8. Repeat for other layers;
9. Put the last lasagna sheet, pure some heavy cream and put a lot of cheese;
10. Cover the pan with foil and put it into the preheated oven at 400F;
11. Cook for 40 minutes;
12. Dismiss the foil and cook for another 10-15 minutes for crispy top.
13. Serve at dinner with side vegetables and enjoy.

Steps: 

1. Boil and prepare plain white rice; 
2. Scramble 3 eggs;
3. In large pan or wok, heat vegetable oil and saute garlic gently;
4. Brown meat if you are using meat. If browning meat, add 1 tablespoon of soy sauce while you're browning the meat;
5. Add rice to hot oil and stir in about 5 tablespoons of soy sauce;
6. Fry rice for about 10 minutes, adding soy sauce as needed to taste; 
7. Add cashews and fry another 3-4 minutes;
8. Add chopped scallions or green onions and fry another 2-3 minutes.

Enjoy!
